        "content": "<p>There are some current PRs that that \"add to the middle\" of the algebraic hierarchy, and we've been observing that it's hard to remember all the bits of infrastructure that should be added when a new typeclass arrives.</p>",
        "id": 231400359,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1616455693
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I thought it might be good to have a library note documenting some of this.</p>",
        "id": 231400382,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1616455708
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not necessarily as a \"tour\" of the algebraic hierarchy, but more of a checklist of things you might want to add when adding new classes, either new leaves, or intermediate steps.</p>",
        "id": 231400406,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1616455742
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Perhaps we could even start linting this?)</p>",
        "id": 231400419,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1616455753
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I made a little start on <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/tree/hierarchy_design\">branch#hierarchy_design</a>.</p>",
        "id": 231400432,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1616455765
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If anyone would like to have a bash at this, please go ahead!</p>",
        "id": 231400448,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1616455785
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wrote down the things that came up in a recent discussion with Eric, but I'm done for the day.</p>",
